# Leash — Data Model

## Entities

### Entity: Harness
The core Rust runtime. Safety gates (deadman, estop, soft-odometry-limit, physical-actuation-gate), pilot token sessions, sim+physical drivers, telemetry broadcast, capability registry.

```yaml
entity: Harness
type: entity
properties:
  role:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: robot
  profile:
    type: enum
    required: true
    values: [sim, waveshare-ugv]
    default: sim
  safety_gates:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: deadman, estop, soft-odometry-limit, physical-actuation-gate
  deadman_ms:
    type: number
    required: true
    default: 400
  soft_odometry_limit_m:
    type: number
    required: true
    default: 0.0
  allow_physical_actuation:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
  allow_untokened_drive:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
states: [planned, mapped, extracted, stabilized, released]
lifecycle: planned → mapped → extracted → stabilized → released
```

### Entity: ModuleGraph
Typed module runtime. Coordinator starts modules in dependency order, stops in reverse. Health aggregation. Introspection exports.

```yaml
entity: ModuleGraph
type: entity
properties:
  module_count:
    type: number
    required: true
  stream_count:
    type: number
    required: true
  isolation:
    type: enum
    required: true
    values: [in_process, cross_process, network]
    default: in_process
  coordinator:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
    description: lifecycle + health aggregation
  introspection:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
    description: graph exports
states: [planned, designed, implemented, tested, active]
lifecycle: planned → designed → implemented → tested → active
```

### Entity: Stacks
Runnable catalog. Composition model for reusable stacks. `leash list` + `leash run <stack>`.

```yaml
entity: Stacks
type: entity
properties:
  catalog:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: sim-http, sim-mcp, compat-http, gated-hardware
  composition:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
  built_in:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
  versioned:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
states: [planned, cataloged, implemented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → cataloged → implemented → tested
```

### Entity: Transport
Pub/sub abstraction and stream processing helpers. Memory + local async backends, latest-value backpressure, quality filtering, and timestamp pairing.

```yaml
entity: Transport
type: entity
properties:
  backends:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: memory, local-pubsub
  backpressure:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
    description: local-pubsub drops oldest messages under receiver lag and reports skipped count
  quality_filtering:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
    description: generic hook for camera/replay frame selection
  timestamp_pairing:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
    description: pair stream items within a tolerance window
  default_backend:
    type: enum
    required: true
    values: [memory, local-pubsub]
    default: local-pubsub
states: [planned, designed, implemented, tested, active]
lifecycle: planned → designed → implemented → tested → active
```

### Entity: Telemetry
Live telemetry streaming. Transport-backed WebSocket and SSE streams. TelemetryStreamFrame includes telemetry, module health, command state, safety state, and viewer-ready visualization data.

```yaml
entity: Telemetry
type: entity
properties:
  outputs:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: transport, ws, sse, json_stream
  websocket:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
  sse:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
  views:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: graph, streams, spatial, command-center
  visualization_frame:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: leash-visualization-v1 pose, path, occupancy-grid, point-cloud metadata, detections, command overlay
states: [planned, implemented, active]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → active
```

### Entity: Replay
Deterministic sensor record + replay. `leash record` + `leash replay`.

```yaml
entity: Replay
type: entity
properties:
  buffer_format:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: leash-replay-v1
  determinism:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
  sensor_record:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
states: [implemented, verified, active]
lifecycle: implemented → verified → active
```

### Entity: CLI
CLI + HTTP server. Subcommands: serve (mcp|mcp-http|http), agent-send, agent-interactive, mcp list-tools/call/status/modules, record, replay, health, stop. REST + WS endpoints plus MCP HTTP JSON endpoints and agent message input.

```yaml
entity: CLI
type: entity
properties:
  listen:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: 127.0.0.1:8000
  commands:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: serve, agent-send, agent-interactive, mcp list-tools/call/status/modules, record, replay, health, stop
  http_endpoints:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: health, capabilities, telemetry, agent/messages, drive, estop, ws/telemetry, mcp/tools, mcp/call, ...
states: [planned, implemented, tested, released]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → tested → released
```

### Entity: MCPServer
MCP stdio server (rmcp) and localhost MCP HTTP JSON control surface. 8 tools.

```yaml
entity: MCPServer
type: entity
properties:
  tools:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: health, capabilities, modules, observe, invoke_capability, stop, estop, capture
  transport:
    type: enum
    required: true
    values: [stdio, mcp-http]
states: [planned, implemented, tested, released]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → tested → released
```

### Entity: UGVAdapter
Waveshare Ubuntu UGV. Feature-gated. Serial JSON-line protocol.

```yaml
entity: UGVAdapter
type: entity
properties:
  target:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: Waveshare Ubuntu UGV
  feature_flag:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: waveshare-ugv
  serial_port:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: /dev/ttyTHS1
  serial_baud:
    type: number
    required: true
    default: 115200
  drive_invert:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
  drive_swap:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
states: [planned, implemented, feature_gated, documented]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → feature_gated → documented
```

### Entity: Bridge
Compatibility layer for existing robot bridge clients.

```yaml
entity: Bridge
type: entity
properties:
  clients:
    type: string
    required: true
  shim_layer:
    type: string
    required: true
states: [planned, mapped, documented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → mapped → documented → tested
```

### Entity: Safety
Runtime safety gates + smoke scripts + policy-gated capability invocation.

```yaml
entity: Safety
type: entity
properties:
  gates:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: deadman, estop, soft-odometry-limit, physical-actuation-gate
  smoke_scripts:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: smoke-http.sh, smoke-mcp.sh, smoke-mcp-http.sh, smoke-physical-gate.sh
  policy:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
    description: safety classes + dry-run/require-token/require-approval/deny gates
  audit_events:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
    description: approved and denied physical actions are structured log events
states: [planned, implemented, verified]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → verified
```

### Entity: ReleasePipeline
Packages for crates.io + GitHub binaries.

```yaml
entity: ReleasePipeline
type: entity
properties:
  targets:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: crates.io, GitHub binaries
  platforms:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: linux-x86_64, macos-arm64
states: [planned, configured, publishing]
lifecycle: planned → configured → publishing
```

### Entity: Bootstrap
Crate skeleton, MIT license, CI, repo provenance.

```yaml
entity: Bootstrap
type: entity
properties:
  license:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: MIT
  ci_platform:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: GitHub Actions
  crate_name:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: leash-harness
  features:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: default=sim+http+mcp, waveshare-ugv, bridge-compat
states: [planned, bootstrapped, ci_green]
lifecycle: planned → bootstrapped → ci_green
```

### Entity: Agent
Model-provider config and input channels. Deterministic no-network CI provider plus validated hosted/local HTTP provider settings.

```yaml
entity: Agent
type: entity
properties:
  providers:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: deterministic-test, openai-compatible-http, local-http
  channels:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: implemented one-shot CLI, interactive CLI, HTTP POST /agent/messages, web form /agent
  message_stream:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: bounded runtime inbox plus agent stream publication
  config:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: agent_provider, agent_model, agent_base_url, agent_api_key redacted, agent_timeout_ms
  ci_model:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
states: [planned, input_channels_implemented, provider_configured, provider_tested, active]
lifecycle: planned → input_channels_implemented → provider_configured → provider_tested → active
```

### Entity: CapabilityRegistry
Shared registry with schema + safety metadata. Routes HTTP, MCP, agent calls.

```yaml
entity: CapabilityRegistry
type: entity
properties:
  safety_classes:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: observe-only, sim-control, physical-stop, physical-motion, physical-high-risk
  policy_modes:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: dry-run, require-token, require-approval, deny
  invocation_origins:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: runtime, cli, http, mcp, agent
  schema_validation:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
states: [planned, implemented, active]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → active
```

### Entity: Perception
Detection/observation adapter. Spatial memory + object registry.

```yaml
entity: Perception
type: entity
properties:
  adapter:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
  spatial_memory:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
  store:
    type: enum
    required: true
    values: [file_backed]
    default: file_backed
states: [planned, implemented, active]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → active
```

### Entity: Navigation
Occupancy-grid + costmap primitives. Sim waypoint router + patrol.

```yaml
entity: Navigation
type: entity
properties:
  messages:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: pose, twist, path, occupancy-grid, costmap, map-metadata
  planner:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
  patrol:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
  sim_only:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
states: [planned, designed, implemented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → designed → implemented → tested
```

### Entity: CommandCenter
Localhost server-rendered web dashboard. Health, telemetry, modules, caps, logs, estop/stop controls.

```yaml
entity: CommandCenter
type: entity
properties:
  feature_flag:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: dashboard
  bind:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: localhost
  views:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: health, telemetry, modules, capabilities, logs, policy, controls
  control_path:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: plain HTML form posts routed through CapabilityRegistry
states: [planned, implemented, active]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → active
```

### Entity: DroneAdapter
MAVLink drone skeleton. Feature-gated. Sim/replay mode.

```yaml
entity: DroneAdapter
type: entity
properties:
  target:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: MAVLink drone
  feature_flag:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: mavlink-drone
  capabilities:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: arm, disarm, takeoff, land, move-velocity, fly-to, observe, stop
  sim_replay:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
states: [planned, implemented, feature_gated]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → feature_gated
```

### Entity: ManipulatorAdapter
Manipulator arm + teleop skeleton. Feature-gated.

```yaml
entity: ManipulatorAdapter
type: entity
properties:
  target:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: robot arm manipulator
  feature_flag:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: manipulator
  teleop:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
states: [planned, implemented, feature_gated]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → feature_gated
```

### Entity: HardwareMatrix
Adapter profile matrix + plugin boundary. Categories, maturity levels.

```yaml
entity: HardwareMatrix
type: entity
properties:
  categories:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: ground, aerial, manipulator
  maturity_levels:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: stable, beta, alpha, experimental
  plugin_boundary:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
states: [planned, defined, documented]
lifecycle: planned → defined → documented
```

### Entity: Daemon
Background run registry. XDG state dir. `leash run --daemon`, status, log, stop, restart.

```yaml
entity: Daemon
type: entity
properties:
  state_dir:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: XDG-compatible
  commands:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: run --daemon, status, log, stop, restart
  graceful_stop:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
states: [planned, implemented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → tested
```

### Entity: Config
Resolved config precedence. `leash show-config`.

```yaml
entity: Config
type: entity
properties:
  precedence:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: flags > env > config-file > defaults
  show_config:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
  agent_provider:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: deterministic-test, openai-compatible-http, local-http
  secret_redaction:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
  policy_mode:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: LEASH_POLICY_MODE / --policy-mode
states: [planned, implemented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → tested
```

### Entity: Logging
Structured JSONL logs. Lightweight resource monitor.

```yaml
entity: Logging
type: entity
properties:
  format:
    type: enum
    required: true
    values: [jsonl]
    default: jsonl
  resource_monitor:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
  cli_json:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
  module_filter:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
states: [planned, implemented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → tested
```

### Entity: ReleaseMatrix
Feature tiers + dependency tiers + CI build matrix.

```yaml
entity: ReleaseMatrix
type: entity
properties:
  tiers:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: core, http, mcp, sim, dashboard, replay, viz, hardware-adapters, perception, interop
  default:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: core+sim+http+mcp
  ci_matrix:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
states: [planned, defined, verified]
lifecycle: planned → defined → verified
```

### Entity: CrossLanguage
Cross-language message schemas + client examples.

```yaml
entity: CrossLanguage
type: entity
properties:
  schemas:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: JSON Schema, protobuf candidates
  clients:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: typed client examples
states: [planned, implemented, documented]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → documented
```

### Entity: SmokeSuite
Full no-hardware smoke suite for release proof.

```yaml
entity: SmokeSuite
type: entity
properties:
  coverage:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: stack-run, daemon-lifecycle, mcp-http, dashboard, replay, graph-export, safety-policy
  no_hardware:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
  ci_integration:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
states: [planned, implemented, verified]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → verified
```

